 DMX’s fiancée Desiree Lindstrom got a tattoo in honor of the late rapper who died early hours of Friday, April 9, 2021  DMX whose real name was Earl Simmons and Lindstrom share son Exodus, 4, whose name was inked on the late rapper’s neck. In a tribute to the late “Ruff Ryders’ Anthem” rapper, Lindstrom got a tattoo that reads “Dog Love,” which is also the name of a song he released in 2006, with an “X” in the same font that the rapper used to stylize his name. She had the ink done by Black Ink Crew artist Krystal Kills.